## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="73d61-114">Le <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.%23ctor%2A> constructeur initialise le <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Id%2A> propriété.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="73d61-114">The <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.%23ctor%2A> constructor initializes the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Id%2A> property.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="73d61-115">L’identificateur doit être unique au sein d’une grammaire donnée.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="73d61-115">The identifier must be unique within a given grammar.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="73d61-116">Le <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.%23ctor%2A> constructeur lève un <xref:System.FormatException> dans les circonstances suivantes :</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="73d61-116">The <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.%23ctor%2A> constructor throws a <xref:System.FormatException> in the following circumstances:</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="73d61-117">`id` n’est pas un nom XML valide, tel que défini dans [Extensible Markup Language (XML) 1.0 (cinquième édition)](https://www.w3.org/TR/REC-xml/).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="73d61-117">`id` is not a valid XML name, as defined in [Extensible Markup Language (XML) 1.0 (Fifth Edition)](https://www.w3.org/TR/REC-xml/).</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="73d61-118">Pour paraphraser cette définition, un nom XML valide doit commencer par une lettre, un trait de soulignement (« _ ») ou un signe deux-points (« : ») et peut être suivie de zéro ou plusieurs caractères NameChar (également définies dans la spécification XML).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="73d61-118">To paraphrase this definition, a valid XML name must begin with a letter, an underscore ('_'), or a colon (':') and can be followed by zero or more NameChar characters (also defined in the XML specification).</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="73d61-119">`id` est « NULL » ou « VOID » ou « GARBAGE ».</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="73d61-119">`id` is "NULL" or "VOID" or "GARBAGE".</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="73d61-120">`id` contient au moins un caractère d’ID de règle non valide.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="73d61-120">`id` contains at least one invalid rule ID character.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="73d61-121">Ces caractères sont : ' ?', ' \*', '+', '&#124;', ' (','), ' ^', '$', '/', ';', '.', '=', '\<', ' >', ' [', ']', ' {', '} ','\\\\',' ', '\t', '\r' et '\n'.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="73d61-121">These characters are: '?', '\*', '+', '&#124;', '(', '), '^', '$', '/', ';', '.', '=', '\<', '>', '[', ']', '{', '}', '\\\\', ' ', '\t', '\r', and '\n'.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="73d61-122">L’exemple suivant crée une grammaire qui reconnaît la phrase « est un état qui a remporté la coupe du monde » suivi du nom d’un pays qui a remporté la coupe du monde.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="73d61-122">The following example creates a grammar that recognizes the phrase "A nation that has won the World Cup is" followed by the name of a country that has won the World Cup.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="73d61-123">L’exemple crée un <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> objet nommé `winnerRule` et transmet l’identificateur `WorldCupWinner` comme un <xref:System.String>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="73d61-123">The example creates a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> object named `winnerRule` and passes in the identifier  `WorldCupWinner` as a <xref:System.String>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="73d61-124">Le <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> objet se compose d’un tableau de nouveaux <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsItem> objets contenant des alternatives pour être reconnus par la règle.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="73d61-124">The <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> object consists of an array of new <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsItem> objects containing alternatives to be recognized by the rule.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
public void WorldSoccerWinners ()  
{  
  
  // Create an SrgsDocument, create a new rule  
  // and set its scope to public.  
  SrgsDocument document = new SrgsDocument();  
  SrgsRule winnerRule = new SrgsRule("WorldCupWinner");  
  winnerRule.Scope = SrgsRuleScope.Public;  
  
  // Add the introduction.  
  winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsItem("A nation that has won the world cup is: "));  
  
  // Create the rule for the European nations.  
  SrgsOneOf oneOfEurope = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("England"),   
    new SrgsItem("France"), new SrgsItem("Germany"), new SrgsItem("Italy")});  
  SrgsRule ruleEurope = (new SrgsRule("EuropeanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfEurope}));  
  
  // Create the rule for the South American nations.  
  SrgsOneOf oneOfSAmerica = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("Argentina"),   
    new SrgsItem("Brazil"), new SrgsItem("Uruguay")});  
  SrgsRule ruleSAmerica = (new SrgsRule("SouthAmericanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfSAmerica}));  
  
  // Add references to winnerRule for ruleEurope and ruleSAmerica.  
  winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {(new SrgsItem   
    (new SrgsRuleRef(ruleEurope))), new SrgsItem(new SrgsRuleRef(ruleSAmerica))}));  
  
  // Add all the rules to the document and make winnerRule   
  // the root rule of the document.  
  document.Rules.Add(new SrgsRule[] {winnerRule, ruleEurope, ruleSAmerica});  
  document.Root = winnerRule;  
}  
```

  
  
